"title": "5150: face",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5150: face",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The main visual characteristic of a person. Facial features are recognisable as uniquely those of a particular person. The face also indicates mood and attitude. The showing or directing of the face towards someone or something may indicate regard, approval or determination, while hiding or turning away of the face indicates the opposite.</p>\n<h2>The face is the main recognisable feature of a person</h2>\n<h3>Examples of facial recognition</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:71\">MAT 26:71</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:66-Mark14:67\">MRK 14:66–14:67</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:56\">LUK 22:56</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:2\">EST 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:9\">EST 5:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:55\">MAT 13:55</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:3\">MRK 6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:35\">MAT 14:35</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:54\">MRK 6:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:36\">JHN 1:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:47-John1:48\">JHN 1:47–1:48</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of failure to recognise faces</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:8\">GEN 42:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:15\">GEN 38:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:16\">LUK 24:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:14\">JHN 20:14</a> <em>There is no evidence to suggest that Jesus Christ's post-resurrection face was different.</em></p>\n<h3>The face may be used symbolically to represent the whole person</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:10\">DEU 7:10</a></p>\n<h2>The physical appearance of faces</h2>\n<h3>Attractive faces</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:15-Song1:16\">SNG 1:15–1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:12\">1SA 16:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:1\">ECC 8:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:4\">DAN 1:4</a></p>\n<h3>Disfigured faces</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:14\">ISA 52:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:12\">JOB 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:29-Matt27:30\">MAT 27:29–27:30</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:65\">MRK 14:65</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:63\">LUK 22:63</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:22\">JHN 18:22</a></p>\n<h2>Facial expressions</h2>\n<h3>The face expresses a person's mood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:5\">GEN 4:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:6\">GEN 21:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:18\">1SA 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:24\">JOB 29:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:6\">DAN 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:9\">DAN 5:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:17\">LUK 24:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:15\">JHN 20:15</a></p>\n<h3>Averting the face may express worship, respect, modesty or shame</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:6\">EXO 3:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:65\">GEN 24:65</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:10\">RUT 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam5:3-1Sam5:4\">1SA 5:3–5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:42\">1KI 18:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:21\">1CH 21:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job11:15\">JOB 11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps83:16\">PSA 83:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:2\">ISA 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:26\">JER 13:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:12\">LUK 5:12</a></p>\n<h3>Setting the face expresses determination</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:51\">LUK 9:51</a> <em>the literal translation is “set his face to go”</em></p>\n<h2>Other gestures involving the human face</h2>\n<h3>Hiding the face from someone as a sign of loss of favour</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:17-Deut31:18\">DEU 31:17–31:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job13:24\">JOB 13:24</a></p>\n<h3>Raising the face as a sign of lack of shame</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job11:15\">JOB 11:15</a></p>\n<h3>Slapping someone's face as a challenge or insult</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:24\">1KI 22:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:22\">JHN 18:22</a></p>\n<h3>Spitting in someone's face as an insult</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:9\">DEU 25:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:67\">MAT 26:67</a></p>\n<h2>Seeing someone's face</h2>\n<h3>An indicator of acceptance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen33:10\">GEN 33:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:3-Gen43:4\">GEN 43:3–43:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:23-Gen44:26\">GEN 44:23–44:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:10\">DEU 34:10</a></p>\n<h3>Indicating confrontation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:11\">GAL 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:24-2Sam14:32\">2SA 14:24–14:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:8\">2KI 14:8</a></p>\n<h3>Not seeing someone's face may indicate rejection</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:28\">EXO 10:28</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of supernatural facial appearance</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:2\">MAT 17:2</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:2-Mark9:3\">MRK 9:2–9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:29\">LUK 9:29</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:30\">EXO 34:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:3\">MAT 28:3</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:5\">MRK 16:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:4\">LUK 24:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:15\">ACT 6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:7-2Cor3:8\">2CO 3:7–3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:14\">REV 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:16\">REV 1:16</a></p>\n<h2>The face of God</h2>\n<h3>As a symbol of blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:25-Num6:26\">NUM 6:25–6:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:1\">2SA 21:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:11\">1CH 16:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:6\">PSA 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:16\">PSA 31:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps67:1\">PSA 67:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:19\">PSA 80:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:4\">PSA 105:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:135\">PSA 119:135</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:29\">EZK 39:29</a></p>\n<h3>Seeking the LORD's face means seeking his will</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:14\">2CH 7:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:8\">PSA 27:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:15\">HOS 5:15</a></p>\n<h3>God's face may be turned away, hidden or set against people as a sign of opposition or removal from favour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:17\">DEU 31:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:10\">LEV 17:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:9\">2CH 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:24\">PSA 44:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:15\">ISA 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:2\">ISA 59:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:7\">ISA 64:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek14:8\">EZK 14:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:23\">EZK 39:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic3:4\">MIC 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:12\">1PE 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:15-Ps34:16\">PSA 34:15–34:16</a></p>\n<h3>People cannot normally see God's face</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:20\">EXO 33:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:30\">GEN 32:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:10\">DEU 34:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job13:15\">JOB 13:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:26-Job19:27\">JOB 19:26–19:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:12\">1CO 13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:4\">REV 22:4</a> <em>In the end all human beings will see God face to face.</em><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:7\">ISA 50:7</a></strong></p>\n<h2>``Face of the earth'' indicates the earth's total area</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:7\">GEN 6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:4\">GEN 7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:15\">DEU 6:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:2\">DEU 14:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:30\">PSA 104:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:2-Zeph1:3\">ZEP 1:2–1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:35\">LUK 21:35</a></p>",
